Description.Display: This package contains the driver for the Killer 1435, 1435s, and 1535 Wi-Fi cards. Wireless driver is the software that helps your operating system to communicate with wireless devices such as wireless cards and network interface controllers.

This package contains the Dell system BIOS update. BIOS is a firmware package that is embedded on a small memory chip on the system board. It controls the keyboard, monitor, disk drives, and other devices. This update addresses the Intel Security Advisories INTEL-SA-00459 and INTEL-SA-00464. A security advisory is a statement when a security vulnerability impacts a product, and a remedy is available for the vulnerability.

This package contains the Intel HID Event Filter driver. The Intel human interface device (HID) driver enables the BIOS to communicate with the operating system through Intel HID messages during an event of any input. This driver enables all input devices to function.

This package contains the Windows Hardware Quality Labs (WHQL) certified application Dell Mobile Connect. It enables Android and iOS users to make calls, send texts, get notifications, transfer files, and interact with mobile apps from the computer.

This package contains the driver for the Intel 8265, 8260, 7265, and 3165 wireless cards. Wireless driver is the software that helps your operating system to communicate with wireless devices such as wireless cards and network interface controllers.

This package contains the driver for the Realtek High Definition audio codec. Audio driver is the software that helps your operating system to communicate with audio devices such as internal sound cards, speakers, headsets, and microphones. This update addresses the Intel Security Advisory INTEL-SA-00354. A security advisory is a statement when a security vulnerability impacts a product, and a remedy is available for the vulnerability.
